obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (72684)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72684&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Provinces`
  line `Tenancy Act, 1898.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to all the territories for the time being administered by the Chief Commissioner of`
  line `the Central Provinces ; and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (72685)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72685&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) the expressions "agricultural year," "malik makbuza," "sir-land," "survey-number,"`
  line
  line `"record-of-rights" and "village" have the meanings assigned to them, respectively, in the Central`
  line `Provinces Land-revenue Act, 1881(XVIII of 1881) as from time to time amended :`
  line
  line `(2) "arrear" means an installment or part of an installment of rent which is not paid on or before the`
  line `date on which it is payable:`
  line
  line `(3) "holding" means a parcel of land held by a tenant of a landlord under one lease or one set of`
  line `conditions:`
  line
  line `(4) "improvement" means, with reference to a holding, any work which adds to the letting-value of the`
  line `holding, which is suitable to the holding and consistent with the purpose for which it was let, and which,`
  line `if not executed on the holding, is either executed directly for its benefit, or is, after execution, made`
  line `directly beneficial to it:`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--It includes the reclaiming, enclosing or clearing of lands for agricultural purposes; but`
  line `it does not include such embankments, temporary wells and water-channels as arc made by tenants in the`
  line `ordinary course of agriculture; and no work executed by the tenant of a holding is an improvement if`
  line `it substantially diminishes the value of any other part of the estate of his landlord:`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--A work which benefits several holdings may be deemed to be, with respect to each of`
  line `them, an improvement:`
  line
  line `(5) "land" means land which is let or occupied for agricultural purposes or for purposes subservient to`
  line `agriculture, and includes the sites of buildings appurtenant to such land:`
  line
  line `(6) "landlord" means the person of whom a tenant holds land, and to whom the tenant is, or, but for`
  line `special contract, would be, liable to pay rent for that land :`
  line
  line `(7) "pay," "payable" and "payment," used with reference to rent, include "deliver," "deliverable" and`
  line `"delivery" :`
  line
  line `(8) "rent" means whatever is paid, delivered or rendered, in money, kind or service, by a tenant on`
  line `account of the use or occupation of land let to him :`
  line
  line `(9) "Revenue-officer" and "Settlement-officer," in any provision of this Act, mean, respectively, such`
  line `Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer appointment under the Central Provinces Land-Revenue Act, 1881`
  line `(XVIII of 1881) as from time to time amended, as the Local Government may, by notification in the local`
  line `official Gazette, direct to discharge the functions of a Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer (as the case`
  line `may be) under that provision : and`
  line
  line `(10) "tenant" means a person who holds land of another person, and is, or, but for a special contract,`
  line `would be, liable to pay rent for that land to that other person. But it does not include a farmer, mortgagee`
  line `or thikadar of proprietary rights:`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--An inferior proprietor is not, as such, a tenant :`
  line
  line `Explanation II.-- The holder of a survey-number in a village let in farm by the Government, or held`
  line `by a gaontia in the Sambalpur District, is a tenant of the farmer or gaontia for the time being.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (72791)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Classes of tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72791&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `There shall be five classes of tenants, namely :--`
  line
  line `(1) absolute occupancy-tenants;`
  line
  line `(2) occupancy-tenants;`
  line
  line `(3) village-service-tenants;`
  line
  line `(4) sub-tenants; and`
  line
  line `(5) ordinary tenants.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (72688)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Presumption as to amount of rent payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72688&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In all suits and proceedings between landlord and`
  line `tenant, the rent payable for any agricultural year by a tenant in respect of his holding shall be resumed,`
  line `until the contrary is proved, to be the rent payable in respect of the holding in the agricultural year`
  line `immediately preceding that year.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (72689)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Date from which order fixing rent operates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72689&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided in sections 66 and 78, an order`
  line `fixing, altering or commuting the rent of a holding on an application under this Act may, as the officer`
  line `making the order thinks fit, take effect from the commencement of the agricultural year next following`
  line `the date of the application, or from any subsequent day, or, if it is made on the ground of increase,`
  line `diminution or deterioration of the holding, from the date of that increase, diminution or deterioration, or`
  line `from any subsequent day.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (72690)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Time for payment of rents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72690&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Rent shall be payable in such instalments and on such dates as the`
  line `Local Government may, by notification in the local official Gazette, prescribe, and, in the absence of any`
  line `such notification applicable to the case, according to the contract between the parties, or, where there is`
  line `no such contract, according to local usage.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (72691)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Rents payable to a number of landlords.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72691&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `When two or more persons are landlords of a tenant in`
  line `respect of the same holding, the tenant, subject to any rule which the Local Government may, by`
  line `notification in the local official Gazette, make in this behalf, and to any contract between the parties, shall`
  line `not be bound to pay part of the rent of his holding to one of those persons and part to another or others ;`
  line `and, subject as aforesaid, those persons shall, if the tenant so desires, appoint one of their number or some`
  line `other person to receive the rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (72692)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to deposit rent in certain cases with Revenue officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72692&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(a) When a landlord refuses to`
  line `accept any instalment of rent payable in money when tendered to him by a tenant,`
  line
  line `(b) when a tenant, in the case mentioned in section 7, desires the appointment of a person to receive`
  line `rent payable in money and the appointment is not made within a reasonable time, and,`
  line
  line `(c) when a tenant in any case is doubtful as to the person entitled to receive rent payable in money,`
  line `the tenant may apply to a Revenue-officer for permission to deposit in his Court the amount of rent which`
  line `he believes to be due; and that officer shall receive the deposit, if it appears to him, after examining the`
  line `applicant, that he had reasonable grounds for making the application, and that it was made in good faith,`
  line `and if the applicant pays the fee (if any) chargeable for the issue of the notice next hereinafter referred to.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (72693)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Effect of depositing rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72693&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a deposit has been so received, it shall be deemed to be a`
  line `payment made by the tenant to his landlord in respect of rent due.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer receiving the deposit shall give notice of the receipt thereof to every person who he has`
  line `reason to believe claims, or is entitled to, the deposit, and may pay the amount thereof to any person`
  line `appearing to him to be entitled to the same, or may, if he thinks fit, retain the deposit pending the decision`
  line `of a Civil Court as to the person so entitled.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or other proceeding shall be instituted against the Secretary of State for India in Council, or`
  line `against any officer of the Government, in respect or anything done by a Revenue-officer under this`
  line `section; but nothing in this section shall prevent any person entitled to receive the amount of any such`
  line `deposit from recovering the same from a person to whom it has been paid by a Revenue-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (72694)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Penalty for levy of anything in excess of rent by landlord.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72694&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `A landlord who, except under any`
  line `special enactment for the time being in force, levies from a tenant anything in excess of the rent legally`
  line `payable shall, on the application of the tenant, be liable under the order of a Revenue-officer, not below`
  line `the class of Deputy Commissioner, to pay as penalty such sum as the Revenue-officer thinks fit, not`
  line `exceeding five hundred rupees, or, when double the amount or value of what is so levied exceeds five`
  line `hundred rupees, not exceeding double that amount or value. Such sum shall be awarded to the tenant as`
  line compensation.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (72695)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Presumption as to payments by tenant to landlord.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72695&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where rent is due, every payment by a`
  line `tenant to his landlord shall, unless the tenant otherwise agrees, be presumed to be a payment on account`
  line `of rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (72696)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Penalty for refusing receipt or giving defective receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72696&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A landlord who refuses to grant a`
  line `receipt for rent paid by a tenant, or grants a receipt but refuses or neglects to specify therein the holding,`
  line `and the period or crop, in respect of which the payment is made, or the amount paid, shall, on the`
  line `application of the tenant, be liable, under the order of a Revenue-officer, to pay as penalty such sum, not`
  line `exceeding double the amount or value of the rent so paid, as the Revenue-officer thinks fit. Such sum`
  line `shall be awarded to the tenant as compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (72697)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Enhancement of rent when productive power of holding increased by landlord.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72697&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in the record-of-rights, but subject to any contract in writing`
  line `between the parties, the rent payable in money by any tenant may, on the application of his landlord, be`
  line `enhanced by a Revenue-officer on the ground that an improvement has been made since the present rent was fixed and in accordance with this Act by or at the expense of the landlord whereby the productive`
  line `power of the holding has been increased.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (72698)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Reduction of rent when effect of improvement ceases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72698&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
