  line
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (72734)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Devolution of occupancy-right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72734&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an occupancy-tenant dies his right in his holding`
  line `shall devolve as if it were land :`
  line
  line `Provided that, except in the districts of Chanda, Nimar and Sambalpur, a collateral relative of the`
  line `tenant shall not be entitled to inherit that right, unless at the death of the tenant he was a co-sharer in the`
  line `holding or unless, failing any such co-sharer, he held land, or was permanently resident, in the village in`
  line `or from which the holding is cultivated, and is in the male line of descent from an ancestor who occupied`
  line `the holding.`
  line
  line `(2) Exemption of occupancy-rights from Court sales.--Save in pursuance of a document duly`
  line `registered before the commencement of this Act, no decree or order shall be passed for the sale of the`
  line `right of an occupancy-tenant in his holding, nor shall such right be sold in execution of any decree or`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) Prohibition of transfer of occupancy-rights.--No occupancy-tenant shall be entitled to sell,`
  line `make a gift of, mortgage, sub-let (except for a period not exceeding one year) or otherwise transfer his`
  line `right in his holding or in any portion thereof, and every such sale, gift, mortgage, sub-lease (other than for`
  line `a period not exceeding one year) or transfer shall be voidable in the manner and to the extent provided by`
  line `the two next following sections :`
  line
  line `Provided that an occupancy-tenant may transfer his right of occupancy to any person who, if he`
  line `survived the tenant, would inherit the right of occupancy, or to any person in favour of whom as a`
  line `co-sharer the right of occupancy originally arose, or who has become by succession a co-sharer therein:`
  line
  line `Provided, also, that nothing in this section shall affect the right of the Government to sell the right of`
  line `an occupancy-tenant in his holding for the recovery of an advance made to him under the Land Improvement Loans Act, 1883, (XIX of 1883) or the Agriculturists’ Loans Act, 1884, (XII of 1884) or the`
  line `right of the purchaser at such sale to succeed to the holding.`
  line
  line `(4) Prohibition of contracts for future sub-leases.--No contract for the sub-lease of holding or any`
  line `portion thereon shall be entered into or made during the currency of a sub-lease of such holding or such`
  line `portion thereof ; and every such contract shall be voidable in the manner and to the extent provided by the`
  line `two next following sections.`
  line
  line `(5) Prohibition of registration of documents transferring occupancy-rights.--Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Indian Registration Act, 1877, (III of 1877) no officer empowered to register`
  line `documents shall admit to registration any document which purports to transfer the right of an occupancytenant in his holding or in any portion thereof, unless the document recites that the transferee is a person`
  line `who, if he survived the tenant, would inherit the right of occupancy, or is a person in favour of whom as a`
  line `co-sharer the right of occupancy originally arose or who became by succession a co-sharer therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (72735)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Rights of certain persons to apply to set aside transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72735&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an occupancy-tenant transfers`
  line `any portion of his right in any land in contravention of the provisions of the last foregoing section, any`
  line `such person as would be entitled to inherit his right in the holding in the event of his death without nearer`
  line `heirs, or the landlord from whom the tenant held the land, may, on application to a Revenue-officer, made`
  line `within two years from the date on which in pursuance of the transfer the tenant parted with possession of`
  line `the land, be placed in possession, subject, so far as the Revenue-officer may, in accordance with rules`
  line `made by the Local Government, determine, to his acceptance of the liabilities of the transferring tenant`
  line `for arrears of rent and for advances made by the landlord or other persons for the necessary expenses of`
  line cultivation.
  line
  line `(2) As among several persons so entitled and being desirous of being placed in possession, the right to`
  line `be so placed shall accrue in the order in which such persons would have inherited the right of the tenant in`
  line `the subject of the transfer if the tenant had died. Failing any such persons, the right shall accrue to the`
  line landlord.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (72736)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72736&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `When any such application as aforesaid is made, the Revenue-officer`
  line `shall issue a notice to all persons who seem to him prima facie to have a right equal or prior to that of the`
  line `applicant, and shall also cause local proclamation to issue in the village in or from which the holding was`
  line `cultivated, inviting all persons claiming to be heirs of the tenant who made the transfer to appear before`
  line `him on a date to be fixed ; and shall, after hearing such of the persons to whom notice was issued as may`
  line `appear, and any other persons who may apply to be heard in the matter, decide who from among such of`
  line `them as desire to be placed in possession is first entitled to be so placed :`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a sub-lease, if the tenant who made the sub-lease appears and pays within`
  line `such period as the Revenue-officer may determine the amount of the consideration, if any has passed, for`
  line `which the sub-lease was made and the costs of the applicant if he would otherwise have been successful,`
  line `the Revenue-officer may replace the tenant himself in possession of the land, if he is satisfied that the`
  line `tenant made the sub-lease in ignorance of the law and is able and willing to cultivate the holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (72737)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Rent of occupancy-tenant to be fixed at settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72737&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rent of the holding of every`
  line `occupancy-tenant shall be fixed by the Settlement-officer at each settlement of the area in which the`
  line `holding is comprised.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (72738)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Fixation of rents during currency of settlement in Chanda, Nimar and Sambalpur.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72738&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) In`
  line `the districts of Chanda, Nimar and Sambalpur, the rent fixed under section 49 shall not be altered during`
  line `the currency of any settlement except under section 13, section 14, section 15 or section 17.`
  line
  line `(2) The rent payable in respect of his holding by a tenant in any of those districts when this Act comes`
  line `into force shall be deemed to have been fixed at the last preceding settlement. of the area in which that`
  line `holding is comprised.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 13, 14, 15, and 17, the rent payable by any such tenant in`
  line `respect of a holding acquired by him after the commencement of this Act shall, pending the`
  line `recurrence of the settlement of the area in which that holding is comprised, be the rent fixed by agreement`
  line `between him and his landlord at the time he acquires that holding, or, in the absence of any such`
  line `agreement, or on the expiration of the term for which any such agreement has been made, a rent fixed by`
  line `a Revenue-officer on the application of either party at the following rate, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `(a) in the districts of Chanda and Nimar, the rate which the Local Government has prescribed for`
  line `occupancy-tenants and caused to be entered in the record-of-rights at the current settlement;`
  line
  line `(b) in the district of Sambalpur, the average rate at which at the current settlement the rents of other`
  line `lands in the same village of similar quality and possessing similar advantages were fixed.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (72739)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Enhancement during settlement in other districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72739&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The rate of rent payable in money by an`
  line `occupancy-tenant in any other district may, during the currency of a settlement on the application of the`
  line `landlord to a Revenue-officer, be enhanced, subject to any rules made under this Act for the local area in`
  line `which the holding is situate and for the time being in force :`
  line
  line `Provided that.--`
  line
  line `(a) an appiication under this section shall not be entertained when, within the ten years immediately`
  line `preceding the application, the rent of the holding has been fixed at any settlement or under any`
  line `provision of the other provisions of this Act, except those of sections 13,14 or 15, or a suit or`
  line `application to enhance it has been dismissed on the merits ; and`
  line
  line `(b) no order shall be made on any such application which is inconsistent with any contract made`
  line `after the current settlement and still in force, such contract being consistent with this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (72740)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Grounds for ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72740&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any contract to the contrary or any provision of a`
  line `record-of-rights, an occupancy-tenant shall not be ejected from his holding by his landlord as such`
  line except,--
  line
  line `(a) as hereinafter provided, for arrears of rent; or`
  line
  line `(b) in execution of a decree of a Civil Court passed on the ground of his having diverted the land to`
  line `non-agricultural purposes or being chargeable with some other act or omission which, by custom not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act or with any other enactment for the time being in force, renders him liable to`
  line `be ejected.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (72741)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Tenant changing land in accordance with village-custom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72741&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `A tenant having a right of`
  line `occupancy in land situate in a village in which the holdings of tenants are by custom liable to periodical`
  line `re-distribution, and exchanging that land in accordance with the custom for other land situate in the same`
  line `village, shall be deemed to have a right of occupancy in the land so taken in exchange.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (72742)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Tenant changing land in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72742&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If a tenant having a right of occupancy in any land ceases`
  line `to hold that land, and thereupon commence to hold other land of the same landlord under circumstances`
  line `from which it may be inferred that the tenant has accepted that other land in lieu of, and on the same`
  line `conditions as, the land which he has ceased to hold, he shall, in the absence of a written agreement to the`
  line `contrary, be deemed to have a right of occupancy in the land which he so commences to hold.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (72743)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Definition of “village-service-tenant”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72743&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `A tenant of a holding who is recorded in the papers of`
  line `the current settlement of the area in which the holding is comprised as holding his land rent-free or on`
  line `favourable terms on condition of rendering village-service, is a village-service-tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (72744)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Devolution and transfer of village-service-tenant’s right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72744&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a village-service tenant`
  line `dies, resigns or is lawfully dismissed, his right in his village-service-holding shall pass to his village`
  line `service-holding shall pass to his successor in office :`
  line
  line `Provided that the Local Government may, by general or special order, direct that, where, on the`
  line `resignation, dismissal or death of a village watchman or patwari, his successor in office is not his heir, the`
  line `village-service-tenure shall cease, in which case the holding shall be retained in occupancy-tenant-right`
  line `by the late village-service tenant or shall devolve in occupancy-tenant-right on his heir, as the case may`
  line `be, at a rent which for the remainder of the term of the current s`
  line
  line `(2) A transaction by which a village-service-tenant attempts to effect a transfer of his interest in his`
  line `village-service-holding by sale, gift, mortgage, sub-lease or otherwise except by a sub-lease for a period`
  line `not exceeding one year shall be void, and the village-Service-tenant shall be liable to be ejected for such`
  line attempt.
  line
  line `(3) The right of a village-service-tenant shall not be sold in execution of a decree.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (72745)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Obligation of village-service-tenant to provide substitute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72745&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `If a village-service-tenant is unable`
  line `to render the service which he is bound to render, he shall provide a competent person to render it for him.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (72746)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Grounds on which a village-service tenant may be ejected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72746&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) A village-service-tenant shall`
  line `not be ejected from his holding except in execution of an order for ejectment passed by a Revenue-officer`
  line `on one of the following grounds, namely :--`
  line
  line `(a) that the tenant has attempted to effect a transfer of his holding in contravention of section 56,`
  line `sub-section (2) ;`
  line
  line `(b) that the tenant has ceased to render the service which he is bound to render, or has failed to`
  line `render it properly, or, being unable to render it himself, has failed to provide a competent person to`
  line `render it as required by section 57 ;`
  line
  line `(c) that the tenant has diverted his land to non-agricultural purposes or is chargeable with some`
  line `other act or omission which, by local custom or the provisions of the village wajib-ul-arz, renders him`
  line `liable to be dismissed from office ;`
  line
  line `(d) that the tenant has resigned, or been dismissed from, his office.`
  line
  line `(2) When a village-service-tenant is ejected from his holding under this section, or when he dies or`
  line `resigns or is dismissed from his office, a Revenue-officer may, subject to any order issued under the`
  line `proviso to section 56, sub-section (1), place his successor in office in possession of the`
  line `holding ; and when a village-service-tenant is ejected from, or loses possession of, his holding otherwise`
  line `than in accordance with his section, a Revenue-officer may reinstate him in the possession of his holding`
  line `and eject any transferee or trespasser who may be in wrongful possession thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (72747)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Definition of sub-tenant.`
  content `A tenant who is not an absolute occupancy-tenant or an occupancytenant and who holds land from another tenant, or from a malik-makbuza, or from the holder of a surveynumber, is a sub-tenant of that land.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72747&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (72748)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Tenure according to agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72748&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `A sub-tenant shall, subject to the provisions of sections 6, 15`
  line `and 16, hold on such terms as may be agreed upon between him and his landlord :`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding any agreement to the contrary, a lease granted to a sub-tenant by an`
  line `occupancy or an ordinary tenant shall not be valid for a period exceeding one year.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (72749)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power to declare sub-tenants in certain cases to have rights of ordinary tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72749&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `—(1) In any`
  line `local area in which the Local Government may by notification in the local official Gazette declare this`
  line `section to be in force, a sub-tenant holding from a tenant who is proved to the satisfaction of a Revenueofficer or Settlement-officer to habitually sub-let the land held by the sub-tenant and to manage it solely`
  line `with a view to the obtaining of rent may, subject to such rules as the Local Government may prescribe, be`
  line `declared by such Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer to have all the rights conferred by this Act on an`
  line `ordinary tenant, and shall thereupon be deemed to have such rights both as against the sub-letting tenant`
  line `and as against the landlord from whom the letter holds :`
  line
  line `Provided that no such declaration shall be made within one year after the commencement of this Act`
  line `or in the case of a sub-tenant holding under a lease registered before the commencement of this Act or`
  line `until an opportunity has been given to the sub-letting tenant to show cause against it.`
  line
  line `(2) When a sub-tenant has been declared under this section to have the rights of an ordinary tenant, so`
  line `much of the rent payable by him as is equal to the rent payable to the proprietor by the tenant from whom`
  line `he holds on account of the land sub-let to him shall be rendered by him to the proprietor direct, and the`
  line `balance shall be rendered by him to the tenant from whom he holds.`
  line
  line `(3) If a tenant regarding whose land a declaration under this section has been made dies without heirs`
  line `or surrenders his holding, the sub-tenant shall be deemed to hold direct from the landlord at the total rent`
  line `paid by him for the land at the time of such death or surrender.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (72750)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Definition of “ordinary tenant”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72750&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every tenant who is not an absolute occupancy-tenant, or`
  line `an occupancy-tenant, or a village-service-tenant or a sub-tenant, is an ordinary tenant.`
  line
  line `(2) In any local area in which the Local Government may, by notification in the local official Gazette,`
  line `declare that the provisions of this sub-section are in force, where a person cultivates land not being`
  line `sir-land under an agreement made with the proprietor of the land and purporting to be an agreement for`
  line `the cultivation of the land by such person and such proprietor in partnership, such person is an ordinary`
  line `tenant of the land so cultivated by him, and, notwithstanding any contract to the contrary, the rent payable`
  line `by him for the land shall be fixed by a Revenue-officer on application made by him or his landlord.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (72751)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Landlord’s right to recover rents determined at settlement as payable by ordinary tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72751&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Settlement-officer shall, unless the Local Government otherwise directs, fix the rents payable by the`
  line `ordinary tenants of a mahal other than ordinary tenants whose holdings consist entirely of sir-land, and,`
  line `on and from the date on which the land-revenue assessment takes effect, the landlord shall be entitled to`
  line `recover only the rents so fixed.`
  line
  line `(2) The rents fixed under sub-section (1) shall be recorded in the proceedings of the Settlement-officer,`
  line `and a copy of the record shall be granted free of expense to the landlord.`
  line
  line `(3) When by reason of the receipt by the land-lord of any consideration, whether in money or`
  line `otherwise, a tenant is holding at a rent lower than that fixed by the Settlement-officer under sub-section`
  line `(1), the Settlement-officer may, notwithstanding anything in this Act, declare him to be entitled to hold at`
  line `such lower rent,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the term is fixed by contract, for the term so fixed or for any shorter period ;`
  line
  line `(b) in other cases, for such term as the Settlement-officer, having regard to the circumstances, fixed`
  line `as fair and equitable ;`
  line
  line `and the term for which the tenant is declared to be so entitled shall be entered in the record made under`
  line `sub-section (2) :`
  line
  line `Provided that in no case shall the tenant be entitled to hold at such lower rent for a period longer than`
  line `that for which the settlement is being made, and, at the expiry of the settlement, he shall not be entitled to`
  line `a continuance of the privilege.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (72752)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Notice of enhancement to be served through Revenue-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72752&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `When a landlord wishes to`
  line `enhance the rent of an ordinary tenant whose holding does not consist entirely of sir-land and whose rent`
  line `is not fixed by an agreement in writing, and the tenant does not agree to the enhancement, the landlord`
  line `may cause to be served on the tenant through a Revenue-officer a notice of the enhancement not less than`
  line `six months or more than twelve months before the commencement of the agricultural year in which the`
  line `landlord desires the enhancement to take effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (72753)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Liability of tenant to ejectment in default of his agreeing to enhancement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72753&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, within the`
  line `period of one month from the service of a notice under the last foregoing section, the tenant on whom the`
  line `notice has been served presents to the Revenue-officer issuing the notice a statement in writing declaring`
  line `his willingness to pay the enhanced rent, he shall be deemed to have agreed to pay that rent from the`
  line `commencement of the agricultural year next following.`
  line
  line `(2) If the tenant does not, within the said period of one month, present to the Revenue-officer`
  line `a statement as aforesaid, the landlord may, not less than ten weeks before the commencement of the`
  line `agricultural year next following, apply to the Revenue-officer to eject the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (72754)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Procedure in ejectment suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72754&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, when an application has been made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `the last foregoing section, the tenant appears and agrees to pay the enhanced rent demanded, his`
  line `agreement shall thereupon be recorded, and he shall not be ejected but shall be liable to pay that rent from`
  line `the commencement of the agricultural year next following the date of the land lords application under`
  line `section 65, sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) If the tenant fails to appear, or if, on appearing, he does not agree to pay the enhanced rent`
  line `demanded, the Revenue-officer shall determine what rent is fair and equitable for the holding : provided`
  line `that, save where in the Revenue-officers opinion the existing rent is merely nominal, the rent so`
  line `determined shall not exceed the existing rent by more than thirty-three percent.`
  line
  line `(3) If the tenant agrees to pay the rent so determined, he shall be entitled to remain in occupation of the`
  line `holding at that rent from the commencement of the agricultural year next following the date of the`
  line `landlords application under section 65, sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) If the tenant does not agree to pay the rent determined under sub-section (2), the Revenue-officer`
  line `may make an order for his ejectment, subject to the provisions of section 88 and 89 and subject to the`
  line `deposit by the landlord, within a month from the date of the order, of the amount of compensation (if any)`
  line `determined as due to the tenant under section 32, If such amount is not so deposited, the order for`
  line `ejectment shall become void.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (72755)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Rent of ordinary tenant regulated by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72755&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `An ordinary tenant shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of sections 13, 14, 15,16, 63, 66 and 78, pay such rent as may, from time to time, be fixed by`
  line `agreement between him and his landlord.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (72756)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Fresh proceedings not to be taken for seven years.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72756&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `When the rent of a tenant has been fixed`
  line `by a Settlement-officer under section 63, or where a tenant has agreed to pay an enhanced rent for his`
  line `holding under section 65, or when a tenant is holding at a rent fixed as fair and equitable under section 66`
  line `or section 78, or when a rent has been agreed upon by contract or consent between the landlord and his`
  line `tenant in respect of any holding, or when an order under section 66 to eject a tenant from his holding has`
  line
  line `become void from failure of the landlord to deposit the amount of compensation (if any) determined as`
  line `due to the tenant under section 32, no notice of enhancement under section 64 shall be served on such`
  line `tenant in respect of such holding, nor shall any further enhancement, by contract or consent or otherwise,`
  line `in respect of such holding be permissible, for a period of seven years from the date on which the`
  line `settlement made by the Settlement-officer took effect, or from the date of such fixation, agreement,`
  line `contract or consent, or from the date of such order for ejectment becoming void, as the case may be :`
  line
  line `Provided that, where a tenant is holding land under a special contract with his landlord at a favourable`
  line `rent for a term of years in consideration of temporary deterioration, or of the labour or expense involved`
  line `in the reclamation by such tenant of the land from waste, nothing in this section shall be constructed to`
  line `prevent a fair rent being fixed or agreed upon after the expiration of the term of such contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (72757)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Grounds on which an ordinary tenant may be ejected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72757&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any contract to the`
  line `contrary or any provision of a record-of-rights, an ordinary tenant shall not be ejected from his holding by`
  line `his landlord as such except--`
  line
  line `(a) as provided in the case of an occupancy tenant by section 52 ;`
  line
  line `(b) in accordance with the provisions of section 66 ;`
  line
  line `(c) in execution of a decree for ejectement passed on the ground that his holding consists entirely of`
  line sir-land.
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (72758)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Devolution of ordinary tenancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72758&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an ordinary tenant dies, his right in his holding shall`
  line `devolve as if it were land :`
  line
  line `Provided that a collateral relative of the tenant shall not be entitled to inherit his right unless at the`
  line `death of the tenant he was a co-sharer in the holding.`
  line
  line `(2) Exemption of ordinary tenant-rights from Court sales.--Save in pursuance of a document duly`
  line `registered before the commencement of this Act, no decree or order shall be passed for the sale of the`
  line `right of an ordinary tenant in his holding, nor shall such right be sold in execution of any decree or order.`
  line
  line `(3) Prohibition of transfer of ordinary tenant-rights.--No ordinary tenant shall be entitled to sell,`
  line `make a gift of, mortgage, sub-let (except for a period not exceeding one year) or otherwise transfer his`
  line `right or holding or any portion thereof; and every such sale, gift, mortgage, sub-lease (other than for a`
  line `period not exceeding one year) or transfer shall be voidable in the manner and to the extent provided by`
  line `the two next following sections :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall affect the right of the Government to sell the right of an`
  line `ordinary tenant in his holding for the recovery of an advance made to him under the Land Improvement`
  line `Loans Act, 1883, (XIX of 1883) or the Agriculturists’ Loans Act, 1884 (XII of 1884) or the right of the`
  line `purchase at such sale to succeed to the holding.`
  line
  line `(4) Prohibition of contracts for future sub-leases.--No contract for the sub-lease of a holding or`
  line `any portion thereof shall be entered into or made during the currency of a sub-lease of such holding or`
  line `such portion thereof ; and every such contract shall be voidable in the manner and to the extent provided`
  line `by the two next following sections.`
  line
  line `(5) Prohibition of registration of documents transferring ordinary tenantrights.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Registration Act, 1877, (III of 1877) no`
  line `officer empowered to register documents under that Act shall admit to registration any document which`
  line `purports to transfer the right of any ordinary tenant in his holding or in any portion thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (72759)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Right of certain persons to apply to set aside transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72759&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `—(1) If an ordinary tenant transfers any`
  line `portion of his rights in any land in contravention of the provisions of the last foregoing section, any such`
  line `person as would be entitled to inherit his right in the holding in the event of his death without nearer heirs,`
  line `or the landlord from whom the tenant held the land, may, on application to a Revenue-officer made within`
  line
  line `two years from the date on which, in pursuance of the transfer, the tenant parted with possession of the`
  line `land, be placed in possession, subject, so far as the Revenue-officer may, in accordance with rules made`
  line `by the Local Government, determine, to his acceptance of the liabilities of the transferring tenant for`
  line `arrears of rent and for advances made by the landlord or other persons for the necessary expenses of`
  line cultivation.
  line
  line `(2) As among several persons so entitled and being desirous of being placed in possession, the right to`
  line `be so placed shall accrue in the order in which such persons would have inherited the right of the tenant in`
  line `the subject of the transfer if the tenant had died failing any such persons, the right shall accrue to the`
  line landlord.
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (72761)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72761&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `When any such application as aforesaid is made the Revenue-officer`
  line `shall issue a notice to all persons who seem to him prima facie to have a right equal or prior to that of the`
  line `applicant, and shall also cause local proclamation to issue in the village in or from which the holding was`
  line `cultivated, inviting all persons claiming to be heirs of the tenant who made the transfer to appear before`
  line `him on a date to be fixed ; and shall, after hearing such of the persons to whom notice was issued as may`
  line `appear, and any other persons who may apply to be heard in the matter, decide who from among such of`
  line `them as desire to be placed in possession is first entitled to be so placed :`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a sub-lease, if the tenant who made the sub-lease appears and pays within`
  line `such period as the Revenue-officer may determine the amount of the consideration, if any has passed, for`
  line `which the sub-lease was made, and the costs of the applicant if he would otherwise have been successful,`
  line `the Revenue-officer may replace the tenant himself in possession of the land, if he is satisfied that the`
  line `tenant made sub-lease in ignorance of the law and is able and willing to cultivate the holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (72762)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Obligation of landlord to confer occupancy-rights on ordinary tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72762&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `any contract to the contrary, the landlord of any holding held by an ordinary tenant shall, at the request of`
  line `the tenant and on the tender by the tenant to him of a sum equal to two and-a-half times the annual rent`
  line `payable in respect of the holding, together with the cost of preparing any instrument required for this`
  line `purpose, confer upon the tenant the rights of an occupancy-tenant in respect of the holding ; and, when`
  line `those rights have so been conferred, the rent of the tenant shall be deemed to be fixed under this Act,`
  line `within the meaning of section 51, at the rate at which rent was payable by the tenant at the date of the`
  line `request and tender :`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenant may, for the purposes of any such request and tender, and the landlord may,`
  line `upon any such request and tender being made to him, apply to a Revenue-officer, or during the progress`
  line `of settlement-operations to a Settlement-officer, to fix the rent of the holding for the purposes of this`
  line `section; and, if it is proved to the satisfaction of the officer that the rate of rent payable in respect of the`
  line `holding is greater or less than the rate usually paid by ordinary tenants of holdings situate in the village or`
  line `vicinity for land of similar quality with like advantages, the officer may fix the rent at the latter rate, and`
  line `the rent so fixed shall for the purposes of this section be deemed to be, and to have been at the date of the`
  line `request and tender, the rent payable by the tenant :/`
  line
  line `Provided, further, that, if the application is made otherwise than during the progress of settlementoperations, nothing in this section shall be construed to empower a Revenue-officer to alter a rent within`
  line `seven years of its having been fixed under any of the provisions of this Act, except on the ground that`
  line `some such change as is described in section 15 has since occurred so as to render the rent so fixed no`
  line `longer a fair rent.`
  line
  line `(2) If a landlord to whom a request and tender are made by a tenant under sub-section (1), refuses or`
  line `neglects for a period of one month to confer the rights of an occupancy-tenant on the tenant, the tenant`
  line `may deposit the sum aforesaid in the Court of a Revenue-officer, or, during the progress of settlementoperations, of a Settlement-officer, and apply to that officer to confer upon him the rights of an`
  line `occupancy-tenant in respect of the holding.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer so applied to, after giving notice of the application to the landlord and hearing him, if he appears, and after making such inquiry as he thinks necessary, may execute any instrument required`
  line `for conferring the rights of an occupancy-tenant in respect of the holding upon the tenant, and the`
  line `execution shall have the same effect as an execution by the landlord.`
  line
  line `(4) Every person upon whom the rights of an occupancy-tenant are conferred under this section shall`
  line `be deemed to be an occupancy-tenant for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall apply to a holding consisting entirely of sir-land.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (72763)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power to direct that suits between landlords and tenants be entered in separate registers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72763&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government may direct that all suits, or any specified class of suits, between`
  line `landlords and tenants as such, shall not be registered in the registers of civil suits kept under the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1882 (XIV of 1882), but in such other registers as it may prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (72764)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Plaint in such suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72764&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) In suits between landlords and tenants as such, the plaint shall, in`
  line `addition to the matters mentioned in section 50 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1882 (XIV of 1882),`
  line `specify the area of the land to which the suit relates, and, where the fields comprised in that land have`
  line `been numbered in a Government survey, the number of each such field ; and, in the case of suits for an`
  line `arrear, the amount of the yearly rent and the instalments in which it is payable.`
  line `(2) When the land to which the suit relates comprises parts of numbered fields or has not been divided`
  line `into numbered fields, an accurate and sufficient description of the land and its boundaries shall be given`
  line `in the plaint.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (72765)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Legal Practitioners’ fees not allowed unless for special reasons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72765&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `In suit between landlords and`
  line `tenants as such, the fees of a legal practitioner shall not be allowed as costs unless the Court considers, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded by it in writing, that those fees ought to be allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (72766)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Set-off when allowed in suits for arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72766&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `No set-off shall be allowed in any suit for arrears`
  line `unless the amount claimed as a set-off has been determined by a decree or order of a competent Court or`
  line `of a Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (72767)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Procedure when ordinary tenant in suit pleads excessive rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72767&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in any suit in which the`
  line `defendant is an ordinary tenant whose holding does not consist entirely of sir-land the tenant appears and,`
  line `at any times before a decree is passed, pleads that his rent is excessive, the Court shall inquire into the`
  line `circumstances of the rent.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court finds that the rent payable by the tenant has been enhanced by contract or consent`
  line `above the rent determined by a Settlement-officer at the current settlement or by a Revenue-officer under`
  line `this Act, or, when not so determined, above the rent at which the holding was first taken up by the tenant,`
  line `or, if the rent payable was determined by a Settlement-officer in proceedings taken before the`
  line `commencement of this Act only after the landlord had refused to comply with the request of the`
  line `Settlement-officer to reduce it, the Court may stay proceedings and refer the case to a Revenue-officer,`
  line `who shall thereupon fix what rent is fair and equitable for the holding. If the rent so fixed is equal to or`
  line `more than the rent previously payable, the Court shall decree the arrears claimed and proved. If the rent so`
  line `fixed is less than the rent previously payable, the Court shall decree against the tenant arrears of rent on`
  line `account of any year only to the extent of the amount (if any) by which his payments for that year fell short`
  line `of the rent so fixed. The tenant shall be entitled to remain in occupation at a rent fixed under this subsection from the commencement of the agricultural year next following the date of the institution of the`
  line suit.
  line
  line `(3) If the Court finds that the rent, in respect of which the plea is made by the tenant, was not`
  line `enhanced or determined in the manner describe in sub-section (2) but was the rent at which the tenant first`
  line `took up the holding from the landlord, the Court shall pass a decree for such sum as may be due at the`
  line `rent so payable, but may, before or after passing the decree, refer the case to a Revenue-officer, who shall`
  line `there upon fix what is a fair and equitable rent for the holding, and, if the tenant pays the amount decreed`
  line `within one month of the date on which the rent is so fixed, he shall be entitled to remain in occupation of`
  line `his holding at the rent so fixed with effect from the commencement of the agricultural year next following`
  line `the date of the institution of the suit.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--Nothing in this section shall be construed to authorize a Revenue-officer to determine`
  line `a rent higher than that payable by the tenant at the date of the institution of the suit except from the`
  line `commencement of the agricultural year next following the date of the institution of the suit, and on the`
  line `formal application of the landlord.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--A statement made during the progress of settlement-operations by the Settlementofficer, and contained in any return or report prescribed by the Local Government, to the effect that a`
  line `landlord refused to reduce any rent, shall be conclusive proof of such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (72768)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Tenants’ improvements how to be treated in fixing rents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72768&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `When the land in respect of which`
  line `an application is made under section 50 or section 51, or for which a fair rent is to be determined under`
  line `section 66 or section 78, has been improved, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, by the agency,`
  line `or at the expense, of the tenant, and such improvement was made during the term of the current settlement`
  line `or the term of the settlement immediately preceding it, the quality and advantages of the land, as`
  line `cultivated land, shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any contract or record-of-rights to the`
  line `contrary, be deemed, for the purposes of any such section as aforesaid, to be the quality and advantages`
  line `which the land would have had and enjoyed if the improvement had not been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (72769)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Interest on arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72769&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `In suits for arrears, interest on the arrears may be allowed up to date of`
  line `institution, at such rate, not exceeding twelve per cent. per annum, as the Court thinks fir.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (72770)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `No appeal in certain suits for arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72770&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `A decree or order passed in a suit for arrears, whether on`
  line `appeal or otherwise, by a Judge of a Civil Court exercising powers not less than those of an Assistant`
  line `Commissioner of the first class as defined in the Central Provinces Civil Courts Act, 1885 (XVI of 1885),`
  line `shall not be subject to appeal, unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount or value of the subject-matter of the suit exceeds one hundred rupees ; or`
  line
  line `(b) a question relating to a title to land or some interest in land, has been determined as between`
  line `parties having conflicting claims thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (72771)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Application for execution by sale of holding or by ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72771&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `An application for the execution`
  line `of a decree for an arrear of rent by sale of the holding in respect of which the arrear accrued or by`
  line `ejectment of the tenant shall contain a statement showing the tahsil and village in which the holding is`
  line `situate, the numbers borne in the village rent-roll by the fields constituting the holding, the rent annually`
  line `payable, and the years in which the decreed arrears accrued.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (72772)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Arrears decreed not to be on current year’s account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72772&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `No such application as is referred to in`
  line `foregoing section shall be admitted until after the expiration of the year in which the arrear, or any part of`
  line `the arrear, accrued.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (72773)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Procedure in execution by sale of holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72773&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) A decree for arrears of rent due in respect of an`
  line `absolute occupancy-holding shall, if sale of such holding be ordered in execution, be executed as if it`
  line `ordered sale in pursuance of a contract specifically affecting the holding, and shall under section 320 of`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1882 (XIV of 1882), be transferred to the Collector for execution.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector executing the decree may, not withstanding anything contained in section 305 of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1882 (XIV of 1882), allow the tenant time in which to pay the amount due :`
  line
  line `Provided that any period, or the aggregate of any periods, so allowed shall, subject to any general or`
  line `special orders which may be issued by the Local Government, not exceed two months.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (72774)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Procedure in execution by ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72774&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) A decree for an arrear of rent due in respect of an`
  line `occupancy or ordinary holding or a holding held by a sub-tenant may be executed by the ejectment of the`
  line `tenant : Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure 1882 (XIV of`
  line `1882), an order for the ejectment of a tenant in execution of such a decree shall be transferred to a`
  line `Revenue-officer for execution..`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue-officer on receiving the decree shall cause a notice to be served upon the tenant`
  line `stating the date of the decree, the amount due there under and the numbers borne in the village rent-roll by`
  line `the fields constituting the holding, and informing him that if he does not pay into Court within a month`
  line `from date the amount due he will be ejected from his holding.`
  line
  line `(3) If the amount due is not paid within the period appointed, the Revenue-officer may, subject to the`
  line `Provisions of sections 32, 88 and 89, eject the tenant or may, after such enquiry as he deems necessary,`
  line `postpone ejectment in order to allow the tenant time for payment : provided that any period, or the`
  line `aggregate of any periods, so allowed shall, subject to any general or special orders which may be issued`
  line `by the Local Government, not exceed in the case of an occupancy-holding or an ordinary holding not`
  line `consisting entirely of sir-land four months, or in the case of an ordinary holding consisting entirely of sirland or a holding held by a sub-tenant one month.`
  line
  line `(4) The Local Government may make rules for the guidance of Revenue-officer executing decrees`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (72775)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power of Court to deal with cases of drought or other calamity in suits for arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72775&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in answer to a suit for an arrear, the tenant admits that the arrear is due, but pleads`
  line `that the produce of his holding during the period in respect of which the arrear is claimed has been`
  line `diminished or destroyed by drought, hail or other extraordinary calamity beyond his control, the Court in`
  line `its discretion may, notwithstanding any contract to the contrary, allow in its decree any deduction from`
  line `the arrear, and direct payment of the amount decreed (if any) in such instalments (if any) as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In any such case the Court may order that the provisions of sections 84 and 85 shall not apply to`
  line `the decree.`
  line `(3) In making a decree under this section the Court shall have regard to.--`
  line
  line `(a) the value of the produce of the holding for the whole agricultural year in respect of which the`
  line `arrear accrued ; and`
  line
  line `(b) the proportion which the amount of rent payable for that year by the tenant bears to that value.`
  line
  line `(4) If in any such suit it appears that the land-revenue of the village in which the holding is situate has`
  line `been, wholly or in part, suspended or remitted on account of drought, hail or other extraordinary calamity`
  line `in respect of the period for which the arrear is claimed, the Court shall presume, until shown, that the`
  line `diminution or destruction alleged by the tenant has taken place.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (72776)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Relief against forfeitures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72776&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `—(1) A suit for the ejectment of tenant on the ground that he has done`
  line `or omitted to do something for doing or omitting to do which he is liable to ejectment, or that he has`
  line `broken a condition on breach of which he is, under the terms of a contract between him and the landlord,`
  line `liable to ejectement, shall not be entertained unless the landlord has requested the tenant, where the`
  line `damage or breach is capable of remedy, to remedy the same, and, in any case, to pay reasonable`
  line `compensation for the damage or breach, and the tenant has failed to comply within a reasonable time with`
  line `that request.`
  line
  line `(2) A decree passed in favour of a landlord in any such suit shall declare the amount of compensation`
  line `which would reasonably be payable to the plaintiff for the damage or breach, and whether, in the opinion of the Court, the damage or breach is capable of remedy, and shall fix a period during which it shall be`
  line `open to the defendant to pay that amount to the plaintiff, and, where the damage or breach is declared to`
  line `be capable of remedy, to remedy the same.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court may, from time to time, extend a period fixed by it under sub-section (2) for remedying`
  line `a damage or breach.`
  line
  line `(4) If the defendant, within the period or extended period (as the case may be) fixed by the Court`
  line `under this section, pays the compensation mentioned in the decree, and, where the damage or breach is`
  line `declared by the Court to be capable of remedy, remedies the damage or breach to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Court, the decree shall not be executed.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
