obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (72782)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Applications to measure or ascertain condition of holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72782&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any landlord or tenant of a`
  line `holding desires that the extent of that holding be ascertained, or that evidence relating to any`
  line `improvement made in respect thereof or to the state of the holding at any specified time, be recorded, he`
  line `may apply to a Revenue-officer ; and that officer shall thereupon, in presence of the parties,--`
  line
  line `(a) make or cause to be made such inquiry as he thinks fit, with a view to ascertaining the extent of`
  line `the holding, and record his finding thereon, or`
  line
  line `(b) (where the applicant seeks to have evidence recorded) record that evidence :`
  line `Provided that no action shall be taken by any Revenue-officer under this section if he considers that`
  line `there are no reasonable grounds for making the application, or if the subject-matter thereof is under`
  line `inquiry in a Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(2) When any matter has been recorded under this section, the record thereof shall be admissible in`
  line `evidence in any subsequent proceedings between the landlord and tenant or any persons claiming under`
  line them.
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (72783)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Limitation is suits under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72783&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) The period of limitation for a suit instituted by a tenant`
  line `other than an absolute occupancy-tenant to recover possession of land from which he has been ejected,`
  line `shall be two years from the date on which he is ejected.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever rent is taken by division of the produce or by estimate or appraisement of the crop, and`
  line `no application is made under section 19, no suit by the landlord for the recovery of the share of the`
  line `produce claimed by him as rent, or the value thereof, shall lie unless such suit is instituted within a period`
  line `of one year reckoned from the date on which the rent instalment on account of the harvest to which the`
  line
  line `(3) In all other cases the limitation of every suit brought under this Act shall be governed by Indian`
  line `Limitation Act, 1877 (XV of 1877) :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in section 7, 8 and 9 of the said Act shall apply to suits for arrears of rent or for`
  line `the ejectment of a tenant, or to suits for recovery of possession by a tenant against his landlord.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (72784)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Jurisdiction of Civil Courts barred in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72784&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `Save where it is expressly provided to the`
  line `contrary, no Court other than the Court of a Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer shall fix, alter or`
  line `commute any rent or call in question any rent fixed by a Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer, or shall`
  line `take cognizance of any dispute or matter in respect of which authority is given by this Act to a Revenueofficer or Settlement-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (72785)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Procedure on applications to Revenue and Settlement Officers, and appeals from their orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72785&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `In fixing rents and disposing of the matters referred to in the last foregoing section, Revenueofficers and Settlement-officers shall, as nearly as may be practicable, subject to the Provisions of this Act`
  line `and any rules made thereunder, exercise the same powers and follow the same procedure as they exercise`
  line `and follow under the Central Provinces Land-revenue Act, 1881 (XIII of 1881) as from time to time`
  line amended.
  line
  line `(2) From every decision or order of a Revenue-officer or Settlement-officer fixing rent or disposing of`
  line `any matter referred to in the last foregoing section, an appeal shall lie as if that decision or order had been`
  line `passed by that officer under the said Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (72786)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Jurisdiction of Civil Courts in suits between landlords and tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72786&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in`
  line `section 95, the Civil Courts shall have jurisdiction in all suits between landlords and tenants as such :`
  line `Provided that.--`
  line
  line `(a) a Judge of a Civil Court of original jurisdiction shall not, unless he is also a Revenue-officer or`
  line `Settlement-officer, hear any such suit ; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Local Government may, subject to the other provisions of this Act, direct that all or any`
  line `class of such suits shall be heard and determined only in such Courts competent to try the same as it`
  line `thinks fit, and not otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (72787)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Recovery of fines and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72787&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `Any sum due as fine or penalty under this Act shall be`
  line `recoverable as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (72789)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power to Local Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417&sectionId=72789&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00119_189811_1675234739417
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government may, by notification in the`
  line `local official Gazette, make rules for the purpose of carrying out the objects of this Act and prescribing`
  line `the practice thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
